## The Five Tenets
This project is organized around five guiding principles:

1. **Reproducibility** — Every environment, dataset, and result can be recreated from scratch
2. **Correctness** — Automated gates prevent bad code from reaching production
3. **Legibility** — The project is understandable to new contributors
4. **Observability** — Every operation produces visible, structured output
5. **Security** — The default is safe; unsafe requires explicit opt-in

## Directory Map
```
├── src/                  Source code (reusable tooling)
├── scripts/              Pipeline steps (numerically ordered)
├── data/                 Versioned data
├── reproducibility/      Docker, environments, infrastructure
├── correctness/          Tests, contracts
├── observability/        Logging, monitoring, runbooks
├── security/             Secrets, permissions, audit
└── legibility/           Style guide, conventions, ADRs
```

